    "name": "same-budget active-selection break-even",
    "statement": "For equal labeled-document budgets and positive random-sampling gain, a candidate policy has higher learning-signal density than random sampling if and only if its heldout-accuracy gain multiplier is greater than its event-compute multiplier."
